def _normalize(value):
    return str(value).lower().replace("-", "_").replace(" ", "_")


def _civil_doc(prefix, section, title, domain, act_name, focus, consequence, related, case_law, procedure):
    return {
        "id": f"{prefix}_{_normalize(section)}",
        "title": f"{act_name} - Section {section} - {title}" if section.replace(".", "").replace("-", "").replace("_", "").isalnum() else f"{act_name} - {title}",
        "section": f"Section {section}" if section[0].isdigit() else section,
        "domain": domain,
        "content": f"""{act_name} provision {section} deals with {title.lower()}. {focus} Indian civil and family litigation often turns on both text and context: the wording of the agreement, deed, relationship, custom, notice, and conduct can be as important as the bare statutory formula. Courts therefore approach these provisions with attention to equity, fairness, documentary proof, and the practical realities of household or commercial life.

Legal consequence and remedy: {consequence} Related provisions and allied legal areas include {related}. Depending on the dispute, the court may grant declaration, injunction, restitution, maintenance, custody, specific performance, partition, possession, damages, or other consequential relief. Procedure matters greatly because limitation, pleadings, registration, evidence of income, and documentary authenticity often determine success as much as the substantive rule itself.

Important interpretive points and case law: {case_law} In practice, {procedure}. For the LAWAI corpus, Section {section} is therefore useful not just as a doctrinal statement but as a working rule repeatedly applied in contracts, property transfers, succession disputes, divorce litigation, maintenance claims, child custody matters, and protection proceedings.""",
    }


